From 4608ca98db24b10d94c36135d801dc70b5e7d6b1 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Kol Crooks <kol.crooks@datadoghq.com>
Date: Wed, 6 May 2026 11:46:40 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] Phase 8.6: workspace registry + LSP via real file:// URIs
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Phase 8.5 gave us syntax-highlighted Monaco diffs but no LSP — the head/
base models were patch-reconstructed and lived under the synthetic
krt-pr-base:// / krt-pr-head:// schemes, which language extensions don't
activate against. Phase 8.6 lets the user register a local clone as a
"workspace" so KRT can serve diffs from real file:// URIs (LSP-eligible
on the head side) plus a krt-git:// scheme on the base side that shells
out to `git show baseSha:path`.

- platform/krt/common/krtGit.ts — IKrtGitService interface (detect,
  detectVcs, getRemoteUrl, getHeadSha, showFile). Lives on the main
  process so the renderer doesn't shell out.
- platform/krt/electron-main/krtGitMainService.ts — implementation,
  spawn() + git CLI. Registered on the krt:git IPC channel in app.ts.
- platform/krt/common/errors.ts — adds gitMissing, gitInvocation,
  gitNotARepo, gitNoRemote helpers + new GhErrorKind variants.
- workbench/services/krt/electron-browser/krtGitClient.ts — renderer
  IPC client via ProxyChannel.toService.
- workbench/contrib/krt/browser/workspace/krtWorkspaceRegistry.ts —
  IKrtWorkspaceRegistry service. Stores { folderUri, folderPath,
  owner, repo, remoteUrl, addedAt } in IStorageService under the
  krt.workspaces.v1 envelope. Includes parseGithubRemoteUrl helper
  for git@github.com: / https://github.com/ URLs.
- workbench/contrib/krt/browser/workspace/krtGitContentProvider.ts —
  ITextModelContentProvider for the krt-git:// scheme. Decodes
  authority-encoded folderUri + ref + path, looks up the workspace,
  and shells `git show ref:path` via IKrtGitService.
- workbench/contrib/krt/browser/workspace/krtWorkspace.contribution.ts
  — krt.workspace.add (folder picker + git remote get-url + parse +
  persist) and krt.workspace.remove (quick pick) commands.
- workbench/contrib/krt/browser/pr/krtMonacoDiff.ts — accept optional
  KrtWorkspace. Per-side fallback chain: registered + status≠added →
  krt-git:// base; registered + status≠removed + file:// model exists
  in modelService → reuse it (LSP); otherwise virtual URI fallback.
  Models we don't own (file:// from the open workbench tree) survive
  dispose() — only models we created get torn down.
- workbench/contrib/krt/browser/pr/krtPullRequestEditorPane.ts — looks
  up the workspace via IKrtWorkspaceRegistry.findByOwnerRepo and
  passes it through to KrtMonacoDiffView for both renderDiffFileSection
  and the tour mini-diffs.

Search filter (workspace-scoped queries) and the workbench-folder-must-
match-registered-workspace gap from the original Phase 8.6 doc are
deferred — Phase 9's chrome work needs to settle first.
